# Memory & session shutdown (Cursor)

Full workflow: `.cursor/MEMORY-WORKFLOW.md`
Protocol: `.obsidian-ai-memory/MEMORY-WRITE-PROTOCOL.md`

## Start of chat

1. Read `.obsidian-ai-memory/02-PROJECTS/session-continuity.md` **first**
2. Then `project-context.md`, `active-goals.md`, `error-memory.md`, `anti-patterns.md`
3. Read latest `01-SESSIONS/` digest(s) listed in continuity file

## End of every chat (before final reply)

You MUST run shutdown unless the chat was read-only Q&A with no repo changes and no handoff needed.

1. Create or append `01-SESSIONS/YYYY-MM-DD/session-HHMM-cursor.md` (template: `templates/session-digest.md`)
2. Overwrite `02-PROJECTS/session-continuity.md` (template: `templates/session-continuity.md`)
3. Update `vault-index.md`, `current-state.md`, architecture docs if behaviour changed
4. `git add .obsidian-ai-memory/` and `git commit -m "memory: YYYY-MM-DD cursor — <summary>"` unless user said not to commit
5. Tell the user: digest path, continuity updated, commit hash or skip reason

## Traceability

- **Continuity** = what the next chat reads first (rolling, one file)
- **Session digest** = audit trail (per chat or appended follow-up)
- **Git `memory:` commits** = history across machines and agents
